Tammy Petersen, News24Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane (Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela spoke at the Cape Town Press Club about the investigations made into ABSA state looting allegations.WATCHThe report was based on an investigation by UK company CIEX in 1997 which probed claims that the Bankorp group of banks, bought by Absa in 1992, had been offered R1.5bn under the guise of a bailout before the dawn of democracy.&nbsp; The leaked provisional report's remedial action includes that Absa should pay back R2.25bn to the fiscus. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.